Requisition No.34721BRJob TitleSr Compliance AnalystAbout First DataFirst Data is a leading provider of payment solutions for financial institutions and merchants around the world.
With over 42 Billion merchant transactions annually and nearly 750 Million credit/debit cards on file, First Data powers the payments value chain in over 80 countries across the globe.
We are proud of our extensive customer relationships supporting over 7,000 financial institutions and the largest merchant distribution network in the industry with over 1,200 partners servicing merchants large and small.Our 25,000 employees are industry experts helping businesses simplify payment processing and improve the customer experience with our broad portfolio of solutions, including: Credit and Debit card issuing and acquiring, STARÂŽ PIN-Debit Network, Point of Sale Terminals and deployment services via our subsidiary, TASQ Technology, Gift Card and Loyalty Solutions, TeleCheckÂŽ
Electronic Check Acceptance Services, MoneyNetworkÂŽ Payroll Distribution, eCommerce and online banking solutions, world-class security services like our new TransArmorsm STARÂŽ CertiflashSM Solutions, and more. First Data. Beyond the Transaction.Business Segment OverviewFirst Dataâs Shared Services organization, including Human Resources, Finance, Legal, and Marketing, supports the companyâs mission to drive our customersâ success with the best products, consultative advice, and ongoing service available in the industry.
The Shared Services teams align with our customer-facing business units in a model that drives cross-company consistency while still allowing the flexibility needed to meet unit-specific goals.Our Shared Services employees bring the domain expertise First Data needs to retain and grow our employee base, drive profitable growth, navigate complex channel partnerships, and build equity around our brand.Job DescriptionThis position supports the Compliance function by managing compliance processes, projects, or programs. This position performs in-depth and more complex research, fact gathering and analysis. This position is routinely involved in addressing regulatory compliance, licensing, business and reporting matters. This position also has a key and substantial role in managing internal document production in response to examinations by business unit regulatory authorities. This position has the ability to independently assess routine as well as non-routine compliance issues and determine if and when to escalate to management, the appropriate legal counsel and/or business unit personnel. Identifies, researches, analyzes and writes business requirements to insure client and market needs are met. This includes working closely with clients and internal departments to clearly understand and address business problems and issues. Responsible for delivery of projects. This includes completion and approval of testing, user documentation, and blended learning plans. Insures business and system development.May, with little guidance, address inquiries or resolve complaints that commit the company financially or otherwise bind the company in significant matters. Problem identification. Understand current business procedures, problems with those current procedures, and possible solutions that use current modeling technology. This includes data gathering and exploration, research into current industry trends, and what competitors might be doing. May be responsible for managing a small-sized budget.Work is performed independently or with minimal supervision. This position has some authority to deviate from existing policies and procedures. Conducts self-initiated advanced research and fact gathering, performs analysis and may make decisions on medium level risk. Delegates tasks to others. May function in a team lead role over projects and/or people. May provide input regarding the performance evaluation of others.Job Specific ResponsibilitiesSecurity ID Badge provisioning at FD and FD MS Singapore. Managing change of access levels for implementation of projects. This will entail provisioning of temporary access and ensuring deactivation of the access at the appointed time. Termination of badges of those who leave the company. Monthly physical security audit of access control (including visitor control), CCTV surveillance and alarm management systems at FD Singapore Gateway for clients, involving coordination work with FD US and local functional stakeholders at FD & FD MS Singapore. Management of Physical Security Quarterly Self Audit Program covering FD & FD MS sites in Singapore, Malaysia, China, Korea, Australia. Management of Half yearly fire drills at FD & FD MS in Singapore. Coordinating & Tracking of fire drills at various FD sites in APAC, excluding FD India. Coordinating Half Yearly Safety Committee Meetings with key stakeholders at FD & FD MS Singapore. Working closely with Admin at FD & FDMS in Singapore on physical related type of crisis, e.g. burst water pipes, air con ducting collapse and etc. Coordinate security violations with Admin and out-source security response vendor (SRS Security) Coordinate works with Tyco and local security systems maintenance vendors for servicing and repair of physical security systems at FD & FDMS Singapore. Track security events in APAC (excluding India) and feed these up to FD Fusion for dissemination to management and affected business entities.Candidate RequirementsExperience in coordinating Physical Securirty related administration duties at multiple site / locationsPreferred QualificationsMinimum of 5 years compliance or other relevant experience required.  A demonstrated aptitude to assess business unit needs and use available resources to meet the needs effectively.  Proven high-level verbal and written communication skills with the ability to provide analytical and consultative direction.  Ability to review complex matters and/or prepare complex responses/documents.  Ability to communicate effectively with all levels of management with the ability to routinely work with highly confidential and proprietary information.  Proven ability to work independently with minimal management supervision.  Ability to identify problem areas and make recommendations to department senior management and business unit personnel.LocationSINGAPORE-SINGAPORECountrySingaporeCitySingaporePrimary Location Address150 Beach Road-#05-01 Gateway West (I4508)Job FunctionSecurityWorker TypeRegular EmployeeFull/Part TimeFull-TimeManager LevelL2: Supervisory / Professional
